---
/**
 * @file privacy.astro
 * @description Privacy policy page detailing cookie-free guidelines and basic server log parameters.
 */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
	title="Privacy Policy — mapaPH" 
	description="Read our clear, straightforward privacy policy. No tracking, no cookies, and zero personal data collection."
>
	<Navbar />

	<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 text-mapa-ink">
		<article>
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-mapa-green tracking-tight sm:text-5xl font-serif">
				Privacy Policy
			</h1>
			
			<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-mapa-ink/80 italic leading-relaxed font-serif">
				We believe in making tools that respect your privacy by default.
			</p>

			<div class="mt-10 border-t border-mapa-contour/60 pt-8">
				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4">
					Zero cookies and tracking
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					The mapaPH hub page (mapaph.com) does not use cookies, tracking scripts, or analytics tools. We do not monitor your behavior across the web, and we do not compile profiles of our visitors.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					No personal data collection
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					We do not collect personal details on this hub. There are no registration forms, contact inputs, or newsletter sign-ups. If you choose to contact us via email or by opening an issue on GitHub, we only use that information to reply to your inquiry or address your feedback.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					Server logs
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Our hosting provider automatically collects standard server logs (such as request timestamps, IP addresses, and user-agent strings) to keep our servers secure and troubleshoot technical failures. This data is static, anonymized, and never linked to individual visitors.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					Individual tools and subdomains
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Because mapaPH is a hub, our mapping projects live on separate subdomains (like lens.mapaph.com). Some of these tools may handle crowdsourced contributions or store basic parameters locally in your browser. Each individual tool is governed by its own minimal data policy, which you can read directly on that tool's site.
				</p>

				<div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-mapa-contour/40">
					<p class="font-sans text-xs text-mapa-clay">
						Last updated: July 2026. If you have questions about these guidelines, you can open an issue on our GitHub repository.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</article>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</BaseLayout>
